<TITLE> 6.16% rise in defence budget </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 07 (bdnews24.com)  Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam has proposed Tk 6,864.25 crore for the defence ministry for fiscal 2007-08, which is a 6.16 percent rise from the outlay for the outgoing fiscal year. In fiscal 2006-07, Tk 5,714.45 crore was proposed for the ministry, which was revised up to Tk 6,465.65 crore. According to the proposed budget, Tk 4,099.54 crore would be allocated for the home ministry. The revised amount for the sector in fiscal 2006-07 was Tk 3,911.99 crore. The finance adviser in his budget speech Thursday said: "To achieve the expected mobility in the healthy and competitive open-market economy, effective law-enforcement and judiciary is a prerequisite." "In the near past, you have witnessed an extreme ruin in the judicial and law-and-order situation. Led by the armed forces, the joint forces have already succeeded in restoring the law and order." bdnews24.com
